<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-08-26T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-08-26T13:36:00-05:00" n="1145" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1145">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4719.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-26T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Mexican Government is most vague and unsatisfactory with reference to
                            conditions in Sonora. I doubt its ability to dominate situation in
                            Sonora. I shall, however, make renewed efforts to-day. Capt. Burnside
                            greatly doubts ability of the Mexican Government to send a force of any
                            degree of efficiency except from the immediate command of Gen. Huerta in
                            Chihuahua.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>